This Power BI project analyzes banking client data to understand financial behavior, credit exposure, and customer risk distribution.

The dashboard evaluates key financial metrics including deposits, loans, income levels, and investment behavior across 3000 banking clients.

Key findings show that total deposits ($2.01B) exceed total loan exposure ($1.77B), indicating a strong liquidity position.

Clients maintain high average incomes ($171K) while maintaining moderate retirement savings and foreign currency holdings.

Risk analysis reveals that the majority of clients fall into moderate risk categories, while premium clients under higher fee structures maintain the largest credit balances.

The dashboard enables banking decision-makers to evaluate customer segments, financial exposure, and portfolio risk distribution.
